-- Israel Stocks: Israel Chemicals, Scailex and Israel Corp.
-- B y   S h o s h a n n a   S o l o m o n
-- 2011-12-19T13:50:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-19/israel-stocks-israel-chemicals-scailex-and-israel-corp-.html
Israel’s  TA-25 Index (TA-25)  increased to
the highest intraday level since Dec. 7, gaining 1.5 percent to
1,101.97 at 3:21 p.m. in Tel Aviv. The measure has declined 17
percent this year.  The following stocks rose or fell today. Symbols are in
parenthesis.  Israel Chemicals Ltd. (ICL)   rose the most since Oct. 16,
gaining 4.5 percent to 37.47 shekels. Israel’s Finance Ministry
said that  Potash Corp. of Saskatchewan Inc. (POT)  is seeking to raise
its stake in the company that extracts minerals from the Dead
Sea. Parent company  Israel Corp. (ILCO)   rose 4.6 percent, the
most since Nov. 30 in intraday trading, to 2,341 shekels.
Separately Israel Corp. said a unit won a $700 million tender to
supply electricity in Peru for 10 years.  Scailex Corp. (SCIX)   declined 2 percent to 16.21
shekels, its lowest intraday level since October 2003. The
importer of mobile handsets said it’s in talks to sell a 50
percent stake in its cellular operations for 300 million shekels
($79 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
